        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "And he arose early in the morning on the fifth day to depart: and the damsel's father said, {b} Comfort thine heart, I pray thee. And they tarried until afternoon, and they did eat both of them.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "And he arose early in the morning on the fifth day to depart: and the damsel's father said, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{b}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " Comfort thine heart, I pray thee. And they tarried until afternoon, and they did eat both of them.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(b) Meaning, that he should refresh himself with food, as in Jud 19:5.",
        "children": []
